HEADWORD: Buffy
<hw>Buff"y</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>Resembling, or characterized by, buff.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Buffy coat</b></col>, <cd>the coagulated plasma of blood
when the red corpuscles have so settled out that the coagulum appears
nearly colorless. This is common in diseased conditions where the
corpuscles run together more rapidly and in denser masses than
usual.</cd> <rj><au>Huxley.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bufo</ent>⟦br⟧
